Module Projet.Biblio
Package Projet.Biblio.User

Class Person

java.lang.Object
Projet.Biblio.User.Person
public class Person extends Object
Model class for a Person. This class represents a person with properties such as ID, first name, last name, address, phone number, birthday, number of loans, and unreturned book status.

    • Person

      public Person(int id, String lastName, String firstName, String address, String phone, Object birthday, int nbremprunt)
      Constructs a Person with the specified details.
      Parameters:
      id - the ID of the person
      lastName - the last name of the person
      firstName - the first name of the person
      address - the address of the person
      phone - the phone number of the person
      birthday - the birthday of the person
      nbremprunt - the number of loans of the person

    • Person

      public Person(String firstName, String lastName)
      Constructs a Person with the specified first and last names. Initializes the number of loans to 0, the unreturned book status to "non", and the birthday to a default date.

    • Person

      public Person()
      Default constructor. Initializes the person with null values for first name and last name.
